{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["UV Pelt"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Relaxes UVs by pulling them out toward the edges of the texture area."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["Make sure the object has UVs and a ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHOP/vopmaterial", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SHOP/vopmaterial"}, {"text": ["Material"], "fullpath": "/shade/materials", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shade/materials"}, " assigned to it. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["You also need to have a texture projected onto a ", {"text": ["model"], "fullpath": "/model", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/model"}, " in order to use the UV Pelt tool. This tool allows you to manually select the boundaries of the UVs where you want the surface to unwrap."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/uvpelt", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/uvpelt"}, {"text": ["UV Pelt"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/uvpelt"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Texture"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["You can easily select loops of edges using the ", {"text": ["Edge Loop"], "fullpath": "/shelf/edgeloop", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/edgeloop"}, " tool."]}], "indent": 8, "role": "item", "type": "tip"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_select.png"}]}], "indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "text": ["Select the edges that will form the boundary of the pelt."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/uv_pelt_after.png", "sche